- !<Text/21bb88cc-d568-46fc-87b2-7bf7293f634b>
  PrefabRemaps:
    []
  Name: Text
  Enabled: true
  RenderOrder: 10
  StretchMode: Stretch
  VerticalAlignment: Top
  HorizontalAlignment: Center
  MeshShadowMode: None
  ShadowColor: {x: 1.000000, y: 1.000000, z: 1.000000, w: 1.000000}
  ShadowDensity: 1.000000
  Text: |-
    Make sure you use you assign your own 
    RenderTarget to ImageVirtContent. Swap the current one! 
    
    This asset will allow you to compose a texture that renders 
    virtual content and background content together. 
    
    A confirmation of this will be seeing an "infinite mirror" 
    effect in the composite texture 
    
    Keep this textue turned off in your application, this is just a reference for you to understand how to obtained a composed image (virtual content and background together) 
  Editable: false
  ShowEditingPreview: true
  TouchHandler: !<reference> 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000
